        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/bedouin-druze-clashes-suweida-al-maqwas.jpg" alt="Sunday's clashes between Bedouin tribesmen and Druze militias began in the al-Maqwas neighbourhood of Suweida city" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>Sunday's clashes between Bedouin tribesmen and Druze militias began in the al-Maqwas neighbourhood of Suweida city. Credits: AP Photo</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The what:</strong> In Southern Syria, fighting broke out between two local groups, Sunni Bedouin fighters and Druze militias, leaving at least <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-30-people-dead?source=website" target="_blank">30 people dead</a>. The interior ministry sent security forces to halt the violence. Hours after the clash, a Druze spiritual leader, Sheikh Hikmat al-Hijri, called for international protection, accusing government forces of supporting extremist Sunni groups (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-about-the-druze?source=website" target="_blank">about the Druze</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The why:</strong> Since the fall of the Assad regime, a transitional government was formed with promises to protect all minorities. But out of 23 main government positions, one was given to a minority representative. This sense of exclusion has led to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-growing-tensions-between-sects?source=website" target="_blank">growing tensions between sects</a>. The latest clash reportedly began when members of a Bedouin tribe set up a checkpoint where they attacked and robbed a Druze man passing through. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
         <strong>The reaction:</strong> Israel, which vowed to protect the Druze minority, carried out <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-spotlight-h1-4-strikes-on-syrian-military-tanks?source=website" target="_blank">strikes on Syrian military tanks</a>, saying they posed a threat to Israel. Experts warn that without genuine accountability and inclusive political solutions, Syria may keep breaking apart along ethnic and religious lines. 
          </p>
      
        </mj-text>
