            ">
           <strong>🇲🇲 Myanmar - Soldiers flee.</strong> Ethnic Karen fighters overran military bases in eastern Myanmar, prompting over 100 junta soldiers and 400 civilians to flee into Thailand. Thai authorities confirmed the soldiers were treated as per the International protocols. The clashes highlight intensifying conflict in Karen State, as the Karen National Liberation Army continues its decades-long fight for self-determination amid Myanmar’s deepening crisis (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-worldwide-10-political-crisis?source=website" target="_blank">political crisis</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
           <strong>🇮🇳 India - Positive trajectory.</strong> Indian FM Subrahmanyam Jaishankar visited Beijing for a Shanghai Cooperation Organisation summit, expressing support for China’s leadership and calling for stronger bilateral ties. Both sides emphasized mutual respect and plan to restart efforts to resolve the longstanding territorial conflict (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-worldwide-11-the-thaw?source=website" target="_blank">the thaw</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
           <strong>🇨🇲 Cameroon - Aging president seeks term.</strong> 92-year-old President Paul Biya announced he will seek an eighth term in the October 2025 election, aiming to extend his 43-year rule. Despite recent internal dissent, he remains the de facto candidate of the Cameroon People’s Democratic Movement. The fragmented opposition faces challenges uniting behind a single candidate (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-worldwide-12-age-game?source=website" target="_blank">age game</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
           <strong>🇧🇪 Belgium - Regional government talks.</strong> Brussels' coalition talks are set to resume this week after a year of deadlock, with six parties looking to finalize a government. An agreement between the liberal party and the socialist party was realized, which could end the political paralysis, as the region mounting monetary pressures (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-worldwide-13-fragmented-politics?source=website" target="_blank">fragmented politics</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
           <strong>🇮🇷 Iran - President allegedly injured.</strong> Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian was injured during an Israeli strike on June 16 targeting a secret underground facility in Tehran. He escaped through an emergency shaft with leg injuries. The strike was part of Israel’s broader offensive on Iran’s nuclear sites last month (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-worldwide-14-injury-update?source=website" target="_blank">injury update</a>).
