        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">What are Golden Visas?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/golden-visa-benefits-global-investors.jpg" alt="This programs is popular among global investors seeking greater mobility, tax advantages, and access to education or healthcare systems abroad" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>This programs is popular among global investors seeking greater mobility, tax advantages, and better education or healthcare systems abroad. Credits: AdS/hamzeh</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The what:</strong> A golden visa allows qualified candidates to gain residence by making an economic contribution to a host country. It is different from citizenship by investment, which gives full citizenship rights. These programs are typically targeted at high-net-worth individuals, as the required funding are high (for example, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-foundations-h2-15-greece?source=website" target="_blank">Greece</a> requires an contribution of approximately $250,000).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The motivations:</strong> The primary purpose of these visas is to attract funding and high-earning individuals to the country, helping boost local economies. Many applicants come from countries like <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-foundations-h2-16-russia-and-china?source=website" target="_blank">Russia and China</a> seeking more liberty, stability, or ways to escape from sanctions. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The criticism:</strong> Critics say that the recipients of these visas are often able and willing to pay more for property than locals can, which can lead to mass gentrification. In response, some countries have tightened rules or ended the programs entirely (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-foundations-h2-17-spain?source=website" target="_blank">Spain</a>). Others, like <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-jul-25-foundations-h2-18-the-trump-card?source=website" target="_blank">The Trump Card</a>, face judicial and tax problems and are for a minimal market ($5M and above).
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
